# .metrics-accept — reviewed waivers for the metrics regression gate.
# See docs/adr/002-metrics-gate.md.
#
# Entry format (one per metric, duplicates are invalid):
#   <metric> <op> <bound>   # <mandatory reason — why this regression is accepted>
#
# <op> is fixed by the metric's direction:
#   <=  for worse-when-higher metrics: large_files, large_functions,
#       may_top_edges, undocumented_exposed
#   >=  for worse-when-lower metrics: doc_coverage_pct
#
# A regression is accepted only while the current value stays within the bound.
# An entry without a reason, with the wrong operator, naming an untracked
# metric, or duplicating an earlier entry FAILS the gate (exit 1).
#
# Default policy: EMPTY — no accepted regressions.
# NOTE: keep the blank line below — it separates this header from any future
# entry, so a bare entry appended at EOF cannot inherit this header as its
# "reason" (the parser treats an immediately-preceding comment block as the
# reason; a blank line clears it).

